<dtccode/>
<dtcname>Blower Motor Circuit</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM000001DTI02OX_01" type-id="60" category="03" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00004RD00001">
<name>DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="E113414E09" width="2.775699831in" height="4.7836529in"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>The blower with fan motor sub-assembly is operated by signals from the air conditioning amplifier. Blower with fan motor sub-assembly speed signals are determined by changes in the duty ratio*.</ptxt>
<ptxt>The blower motor control controls the blower with fan motor sub-assembly speed. The blower motor control reads the signal from the air conditioning amplifier assembly and controls rotation and speed.</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>*: The duty ratio is the ratio of the blower with fan motor sub-assembly on time (A) to the total of the blower with fan motor sub-assembly on and off time (A + B).</ptxt>
</atten4>
</content5>
</subpara>
